-- Vietnam Stocks: Bien Hoa Sugar, Hung Vuong, Societe de Bourbon
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-04-27T05:38:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/vietnam-stocks-bien-hoa-sugar-hung-vuong-societe-de-bourbon.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11:30 a.m. break in  Ho Chi
Minh City . The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi
Minh City Stock Exchange, rose 0.7 percent to 473.39, set for
the highest close since May.  Sugar Stocks:  Societe de Bourbon Tay Ninh  (SBT VN),
Vietnam’s biggest listed sugar company, rose 2.4 percent to
21,000 dong.  Bien Hoa Sugar Joint-Stock Co. (BHS)  , jumped 4.6
percent to 20,400 dong.  Ninh Hoa Sugar Joint-Stock Co. (NHS)  
gained 3.1 percent to 26,600 dong.  An increase in sugar consumption may lead to a shortage by
August, Tuoi Tre newspaper reported today, citing a report from
the Agriculture Ministry. Sugar use increased by about 150,000
metric tons in the past four weeks, compared with the same
period last year, after companies boosted purchases for export
to China, according to the report. Vietnam’s sugar stockpile is
currently at 355,000 tons, 169,000 tons less than a year ago.  Hung Vuong Corp. (HVG)  , the third-largest listed seafood
producer and exporter, gained 2.3 percent, to 36,000 dong. Hung
Vuong plans to pay a dividend of 1,000 dong a share on Jun. 29,
it said on the exchange’s website.  To contact the Bloomberg News staff on this story:
